{[show NS]

South is to play 6NT. West leads the \DJ. East takes the \DA and returns the \D2.

Make a Plan, then click NEXT. [NEXT]

[show NESW]

[clear-commentary]

Your 4 \S tricks, 2 \H tricks, 1 \D trick and 4 \C tricks are very easy to find. But that's only 11, so where in the world can you possibly find number 12?

With all those high \Ds falling on the first two tricks dummy's \D 9 has become a threat against West. If it should happen that West also holds the only \H stopper you can squeeze him in the red suits. [NEXT]

[PLAY N:D7,N:D3,E:DA,E:D2,S:DK,S:DQ,W:DJ,W:D4]

[clear-commentary]

You are going to now run your black suit winners, but take the \Cs first so you can be playing winners from your hand when you squeeze West.

On the last 2 \Cs West discards a \D and a \H. [NEXT]

[PLAY N:CA,N:CK,N:CQ,N:CJ,E:D5,E:C9,E:C5,E:C2,S:CT,S:C8,S:C7,S:C4,W:H2,W:D8,W:C6,W:C3]

[clear-commentary]

Now come to your hand with the \SA and play the \S K Q.

You discard a small \H from dummy while West follows suit three times. [NEXT]

[showcards N:HA,HK,H8,D9 E:S9,HJ,H4,D6 S:SJ,H9,H5,H3 W:HQ,HT,H7,DT]

[PLAY N:ST,N:S6,N:H6,E:S7,E:S4,E:S2,S:SA,S:SK,S:SQ,W:S8,W:S5,W:S3]

[clear-commentary]

It is time.

Play your \SJ and watch what West discards.

If he holds on to the \D10 you will discard dummy's useless \D9 and hope the \Hs all fall under the \H A K.

If he discards the \D10 then you throw dummy's small \H and dummy wins the last three tricks.}
[Play "W"]DJ

