{[show NS]

South is to play 6NT. West leads the \HJ. East wins the \HA and returns the \H2.

Make a Plan, then click NEXT. [NEXT]

[show NESW]

[clear-commentary]

With only 11 winners you need to find one more and your prospects are quite slim.

No matter how the \Ss split only one defender will hold the Guard because only one defender can have as many as 4. IF (it's a big IF) that same defender holds the \CK then you can squeeze him.

Can you see how the squeeze is going to work? [NEXT]

[PLAY N:H7,N:H5,E:HA,E:H2,S:HK,S:HQ,W:HJ,W:H3]

[clear-commentary]

If you try to run your \Ds right away you will have a problem with your \CQ later on. It will be no good as a Threat card because you will have no entry back to your hand.

The solution is the Vienna Coup. Play a \C to the \CA at trick 3.

Then start running the \D suit. [NEXT]

[PLAY N:DT,N:D7,N:D2,N:CA,N:C7,N:C5,E:H8,E:H4,E:D5,E:C9,E:C4,E:C2,S:DA,S:DK,S:DQ,S:DJ,S:D9,S:C3,W:H9,W:H6,W:D8,W:D6,W:D4,W:C6]

[clear-commentary]

This is the situation after you have unblocked dummy's \CA and then played 5 \D winners.

So far neither defender is hurting, but that is about to change.

You play your \D3 and discard dummy's \CT.

East is squeezed. He can't throw his \CK without letting your \CQ become a winner. But if he discards a \S dummy's \S5 will win the last trick. This is soooo much fun.}
[Play "W"]HJ

