[PLAY N:S2,N:CQ,N:C4,N:C3,E:S6,E:C9,E:C7,E:C5,S:SK,S:CA,S:CK,S:C2,W:SQ,W:S3,W:CT,W:C6]

[clear-commentary]

Now you know East guards the \Cs.

Before tackling \Ds, see what you can discover about \Ss.

Play the \SA. East discards a \H. [NEXT]

[PLAY N:S5,E:H3,S:SA,W:S8]

[clear-commentary]

East guards the \Cs. West guards the \Ss. Nobody can guard the \Hs.

Play 4 rounds of \Ds. [NEXT]

